The paper deals with propositional proof systems and their complexity, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves the use of linear equations and multilinear formulas, which are relevant to topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and linear algebra (cs.LO). The paper also uses interpolation, which is a technique in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper connects resolution over linear equations with cutting planes, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG).
